-- Japan May Station Troops on Yonaguni as China Tensions Rise, Nikkei Says
-- B y   F e r g u s   M a g u i r e
-- 2010-09-28T21:55:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/japan-may-station-troops-on-yonaguni-as-china-tensions-rise-nikkei-says.html
Japan’s government is considering
stationing defense personnel on Yonaguni Island, the westernmost
island governed by Okinawa prefecture, Nikkei English News said,
without citing anyone.   The plan follows an increase in activity by China’s navy
and this month’s collision of a Chinese fishing boat with
Japan’s coast guard, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fergus Maguire at 
 fmaguire@bloomberg.net  